            <h2>Our Vision: Leaders Who Understand and Transform Systems</h2>
            <p>We envision a future where political leaders possess a deep understanding of complex systems, are driven by a commitment to addressing root causes, and have a proven track record of fostering collaboration. They see the nation not as broken machinery but as a living, evolving system capable of renewal and growth.</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Deep understanding of complex systems</li>
                <li>Commitment to addressing root causes</li>
                <li>Proven track record of collaboration</li>
                <li>Focus on building resilient and equitable systems</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section id="process" class="content-section">
            <h2>The Process: A National Leadership Discovery</h2>
            <p>Our initiative involves a multi-phase process to identify, vet, connect, and ultimately elevate systems change leaders.</p>
            <ol>
                <li><strong>National Mapping & Identification:</strong> Identifying individuals leading systems change efforts.</li>
                <li><strong>Vetting & Initial Assessment:</strong> Evaluating candidates based on key criteria.</li>
                <li><strong>Connection & Collaborative Challenge:</strong> Bringing candidates together for collaborative problem-solving.</li>
                <li><strong>The Tournament of Systems Solutions:</strong> A public demonstration of their skills.</li>
                <li><strong>Elevation & Transition to Candidacy:</strong> Supporting top candidates in their political journey.</li>
            </ol>
            <p>We are currently in the <strong>National Mapping & Identification</strong> phase.</p>
        </section>

